FBIS3-49624 "dreeu008__a94035" FBIS-EEU-94-008-A Document Type:Daily Report 12 January 1994 ANNEX Kosovo Bukoshi Urges `Immediate' NATO Action in Kosova AU1101182994 Tirana ATA in English 1146 GMT 11 Jan 94 AU1101182994 Tirana ATA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tirana, January 11 (ATA) -- Kosova Premier Bujar Bukoshi sent a letter to the premiers of NATO member states appealing on NATO to exercise its influence to take the following actions: Return of international human rights observers in Kosova, stationing of peace-keeping forces in the region, and continue to put pressure on Serbia and bring to the court all the criminals of mankind. Bukoshi observes that lack of immediate action in this regard means postponement of the inevitable, whose price will be dearer.
